title Telecoms Sovereignty (Nation-State View, Oct 2022)
style wardley

// Anchor set U — four user types per the scenario
anchor Government [0.98, 0.35]
anchor The Collective [0.97, 0.30]
anchor Corporations [0.96, 0.55]
anchor People [0.95, 0.70]

// Sovereignty pillars — the needs the anchors want satisfied
component Territorial Sovereignty [0.90, 0.30]
component Political Sovereignty [0.89, 0.28]
component Cultural Sovereignty [0.88, 0.32]
component Economic Sovereignty [0.87, 0.45]
component Digital Sovereignty [0.86, 0.35]
component CNI Sovereignty [0.85, 0.40]

// Theatre / awareness layer — what a sovereign must SEE
component Land-Sea-Air-Space Awareness [0.80, 0.32]
component Supply-Chain Awareness [0.78, 0.20]
component Peering Awareness [0.76, 0.55]

// Access devices (directly used by People / Corporations)
component Smartphones [0.78, 0.88]
component Computers [0.76, 0.88]
component Radio / TV [0.74, 0.90]
component Satellite Phones [0.70, 0.55]
component IoT Devices [0.68, 0.65]

// Access networks
component Mobile Towers [0.62, 0.78]
component Fixed Cable [0.60, 0.82]
component Satellite Access [0.58, 0.55]
component Launch Vehicles [0.40, 0.45]

// Network equipment and topology
component Fixed Network Equipment [0.52, 0.78]
component Mobile Network Equipment [0.50, 0.78]
component Network Topology (Fixed) [0.48, 0.68]
component Network Topology (Mobile) [0.46, 0.68]

// Control / governance layer
component DNS-over-HTTPS [0.58, 0.80]
component Nation-State Firewall [0.56, 0.45]
component SIMs / eSIMs [0.64, 0.88]
component Geofencing [0.54, 0.55]

// Expertise (Knowledge layer)
component Telecoms Expertise [0.40, 0.40]
component Standards Bodies (3GPP/ITU) [0.38, 0.72]

// Underlying reality
component Compute [0.30, 0.85]
component Power [0.25, 0.90]
component Physical Supply Chain [0.22, 0.55]
component Information Supply Chain [0.20, 0.55]
component Space (Orbits) [0.18, 0.45]
component Geography [0.12, 0.95]

// ---------- Dependencies ----------

// Anchors -> pillars
Government->Territorial Sovereignty
Government->Political Sovereignty
Government->Digital Sovereignty
Government->CNI Sovereignty
The Collective->Cultural Sovereignty
The Collective->Political Sovereignty
Corporations->Economic Sovereignty
Corporations->Digital Sovereignty
People->Cultural Sovereignty
People->Digital Sovereignty

// Pillars -> theatre/awareness and stack
Territorial Sovereignty->Land-Sea-Air-Space Awareness
Territorial Sovereignty->Geography
Political Sovereignty->Nation-State Firewall
Political Sovereignty->Supply-Chain Awareness
Cultural Sovereignty->Radio / TV
Cultural Sovereignty->Smartphones
Economic Sovereignty->Peering Awareness
Economic Sovereignty->Standards Bodies (3GPP/ITU)
Digital Sovereignty->DNS-over-HTTPS
Digital Sovereignty->Nation-State Firewall
Digital Sovereignty->SIMs / eSIMs
Digital Sovereignty->Geofencing
CNI Sovereignty->Fixed Network Equipment
CNI Sovereignty->Mobile Network Equipment
CNI Sovereignty->Power
CNI Sovereignty->Compute

// Awareness -> reality
Land-Sea-Air-Space Awareness->Geography
Land-Sea-Air-Space Awareness->Space (Orbits)
Supply-Chain Awareness->Physical Supply Chain
Supply-Chain Awareness->Information Supply Chain
Peering Awareness->Standards Bodies (3GPP/ITU)

// Devices -> access networks
Smartphones->Mobile Towers
Smartphones->SIMs / eSIMs
Computers->Fixed Cable
Radio / TV->Mobile Towers
Satellite Phones->Satellite Access
IoT Devices->Mobile Towers
IoT Devices->Fixed Cable

// Access networks -> equipment / topology / reality
Mobile Towers->Mobile Network Equipment
Mobile Towers->Network Topology (Mobile)
Fixed Cable->Fixed Network Equipment
Fixed Cable->Network Topology (Fixed)
Satellite Access->Launch Vehicles
Satellite Access->Space (Orbits)
Launch Vehicles->Physical Supply Chain

// Equipment / topology -> reality
Fixed Network Equipment->Compute
Fixed Network Equipment->Power
Fixed Network Equipment->Physical Supply Chain
Mobile Network Equipment->Compute
Mobile Network Equipment->Power
Mobile Network Equipment->Physical Supply Chain
Network Topology (Fixed)->Geography
Network Topology (Mobile)->Geography

// Control layer -> underpinnings
DNS-over-HTTPS->Compute
DNS-over-HTTPS->Information Supply Chain
Nation-State Firewall->Compute
Nation-State Firewall->Telecoms Expertise
SIMs / eSIMs->Physical Supply Chain
Geofencing->Network Topology (Mobile)

// Expertise ties
Telecoms Expertise->Standards Bodies (3GPP/ITU)

// Inertia markers — components that are sticky by Oct 2022
component Copper Last-Mile [0.45, 0.75] inertia
Fixed Cable->Copper Last-Mile
// Sunk capital + human capital inertia forms dominate this one

// Evolution movements (scenario, not forecast)
evolve Satellite Access 0.75
evolve Nation-State Firewall 0.70
evolve Launch Vehicles 0.65

// Strategic notes
note Sovereign-controllable zone [0.82, 0.18]
note Foreign-dependent chokepoints [0.25, 0.80]
